metadata.title: MD Helicopters MD 500
aws::graph::propositions: The MD 500 is widely operated by private individuals, companies and law enforcement agencies around the world.
Belgium's Federal Police operates the MD 500.
Colombia's National Police operates the MD 500.
Costa Rica's Air Vigilance Service operates the MD 500.
Ecuador's National Police operates the MD 500.
El Salvador's Salvadoran Air Force operates the MD 500.
Finland's Utti Jaeger Regiment operates the MD 500.
Honduras's Honduran Air Force operates the MD 500.
Hungary's Hungarian Police operates the MD 500.
Indonesia's Pelita Air operates the MD 500.
Indonesian Air Force received 12 ex-Pelita Air Hughes 500C in 1982.
The Hughes 500C helicopters were retired from service in the Indonesian Air Force.
Iraqi Kurdistan's Kurdistan Region Police operates the MD 500.
Italy's Guardia di Finanza operates the MD 500.
Italy's State Forestry Corps operates the MD 500.
Philippine Air Force operates 1 unit of MD-500E trainer helicopter.
The MD-500E trainer helicopter was transferred to Philippine Air Force from Department of Public Works and Highways.
